      • getCommands

        public Set<Command> getCommands()
        Returns the underlying set of Commands registered with this CommandManager.

        The set returned is the same set as the one held by this CommandManager; changes to it are reflected in command execution. It is recommended to use the add/remove methods instead of directly modifying the returned set.

        Returns:
        this CommandManager's commands

      • getHelpGenerator

        public Optional<HelpGenerator> getHelpGenerator()
        Returns the HelpGenerator used by help commands registered under this CommandManager.

        If no HelpGenerator is assigned, commands executed will not have a help command. Help registration is dynamic, however; commands will receive their help command as soon as the CommandManager that owns them receives a HelpGenerator.

        Returns:
        the HelpGenerator used by help commands registered under this CommandManager

      • setHelpGenerator

        public void setHelpGenerator(HelpGenerator helpGen)
        Sets the HelpGenerator used by help commands registered under this CommandManager.

        Can be set to null to disable help commands.

        Parameters:
        helpGen - the HelpGenerator used by help commands registered under this CommandManager

      • getPreExecutor

        public Function<CommandContext,Optional<String>> getPreExecutor()
        Returns the pre-executor used for Commands ran with this CommandManager.

        The pre-executor is called before calling the executor, allowing one to do checks on the context of the command before allowing it to be ran. Should the pre-executor return a non-empty Optional, it is assumed that the it does not want the command to be ran. A command running in dry mode will silently fail, but would otherwise throw a CommandException with the message produced by the pre-executor.

        The default pre-executor always returns an empty Optional. This method cannot return null.

        Returns:
        this CommandManager's pre-executor

      • setPreExecutor

        public void setPreExecutor(Function<CommandContext,Optional<String>> preExec)
        Sets the pre-executor used for Commands ran with this CommandManager.

        Passing null will set the default pre-executor (which always returns an empty Optional).

        Parameters:
        preExec - the new pre-executor, or null to use default
